definition: to help/to assist/to support/for sb (i.e. as a help)/hired (as worker)/side (of pail, boat etc)/outer layer/upper (of a shoe)/group/gang/clique/party/secret society

sentences.english: Grandpa leaned slowly toward Grandma and gave her a lingering kiss on her wrinkled cheek.
sentences.chinese: 老爺爺慢慢斜過身來在她的腮幫上給他一個長吻。

sentences.english: What do baboons keep in their cheek pouches?
sentences.chinese: 狒狒把什麼儲存在腮幫子裏？

sentences.english: The lawyer sucked in his cheeks whenever he was thinking hard.
sentences.chinese: 這位律師每當沉思時便撮緊腮幫子。

sentences.english: While the air is being forced from the cheeks, inhale quickly and deeply through the nose.
sentences.chinese: 當空氣被壓出腮幫的同時，鼻子快速深吸氣。

sentences.english: His cheek is stuffed with pear.
His cheek is stuffed with apple.
sentences.chinese: 他的腮幫子裏塞滿蘋果。

sentences.english: They will be frolicking with each other pro cheeks.
sentences.chinese: 它們會嬉笑打鬧，相互親腮幫子。

sentences.english: I plumped out my cheeks in an expression of indignation.
sentences.chinese: 我鼓起腮幫子以表示憤慨。
